==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elzevir
<hw>El"ze*vir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bibliog.)</fld>
<def>Applied to books or editions (esp. of the Greek New Testament and
the classics) printed and published by the Elzevir family at Amsterdam,
Leyden, etc., from about 1592 to 1680; also, applied to a round open
type introduced by them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>Elzevir</qex> editions are valued for their neatness, and
the elegant small types used.</q> <rj><qau>Brande & C.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>'Em</ent>⟦br⟧
